# Enterprise Architecture

This project follows Enterprise Architecture principles.

Architecture is the highest priority after business requirements.

Never introduce architectural inconsistencies.

---

# Architecture Style

The project follows:

- Modular Monolith
- Domain Driven Design
- Clean Architecture
- Feature-first organization
- SOLID
- DRY
- KISS
- YAGNI

---

# Layer Separation

Every feature is divided into:

Presentation

↓

Application

↓

Domain

↓

Infrastructure

Dependencies always point inward.

---

# Module Independence

Business modules should remain independent.

Communication occurs only through well-defined interfaces.

Avoid tight coupling.

---

# Composition

Prefer composition over inheritance.

Favor explicit dependencies.

Avoid hidden behavior.

---

# Public Contracts

Modules communicate only through public contracts.

Never bypass boundaries.

---

# Architecture Goals

Prioritize:

- Maintainability
- Scalability
- Testability
- Extensibility
- Reliability
- Simplicity

---

# Forbidden

Never:

- Mix business logic with infrastructure.
- Create circular dependencies.
- Couple unrelated modules.
- Duplicate business rules.
- Leak implementation details.